data.title: Nathan Phelps – Advanced Orthopedic Newberg Physical Therapy
data.text:
Nathan was 1 of only 64 specialists in the state at the time of his examination, which is less than 4% of the current treating physical therapists. He is also a teaching assistant in orthopedics at George Fox University Doctor of Physical Therapy Program. Keeping him up to date on the most current treatment approaches.

Nathan received his bachelor’s degree in Exercise and Sports Science from Oregon State University, and then went to Chapman University where he graduated with his Doctorate in Physical Therapy. Patients who are experiencing musculoskeletal pain, neurological pain or need post-operative rehab would greatly benefit from his expertise.

Nathan also has advanced knowledge in diagnostics, manual therapy, and therapeutic exercise. He combines a whole-body approach through a differential diagnostic evaluation to treat your specific pain condition. This provides you the best opportunity to reduce/eliminate your pain from daily living.
